Fix unreadable white-on-white text in audit module (Task #26)

Problem: All 28 /audit/* pages were built for a dark theme (text-white,
text-slate-50/100/200/300/400, bg-slate-700/800/900 and many alpha
variants). They now render on a light surface under the platform-ui
wrapper, producing white/near-white text on white backgrounds.

Root cause: globals.css already contained a dark->light conversion block
(`.audit-light`) but (a) it was never applied — the audit layout used
`bg-slate-950 text-slate-200` instead — and (b) its conversions only
covered a few enumerated classes, missing the alpha/hover variants and
`text-slate-50` that the pages actually use.

Fix (CSS only, no per-page edits, no redesign):
- frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/audit/layout.tsx wraps content in
  `audit-light ... !bg-[var(--color-subtle)]` (the ! forces the subtle
  gray canvas over `.audit-light{background:#fff}`). This activates the
  conversion for every audit page + their inline (non-portal) modals.
- frontend/src/app/globals.css `.audit-light` block expanded from brittle
  enumerated class lists to attribute-substring selectors so ALL shades,
  alpha variants and responsive/state prefixes are covered:
  * backgrounds: [class*="bg-slate-6|7|8|9"] -> #fff
  * borders:     [class*="border-slate-5|6|7|8|9"] -> #e5e7eb
  * text:        added text-slate-50 to the 50-600 -> #4b5563 rule
  * hover bg:    [class*="hover:bg-slate-"]:hover -> #f3f4f6 (preserves
    hover feedback; specificity 0,3,0 beats base 0,2,0)
  * hover text:  [class*="hover:text-slate-"]:hover -> #4b5563
  * group-hover: [class*="group-hover:text-white"] -> #111827 (both rest
    and hover, overrides Tailwind's non-important group-hover rule)
- Colored-button/badge white-text safelist, the bg-slate-700/800.text-white
  chip rule, and `.audit-light .text-white -> #111827` are preserved.

Scope / deviations:
- Admin and ComplyChat are light-built and only use text-white on colored
  buttons (already correct); intentionally left unchanged to avoid
  regressions.
- Left a few subtle accents unconverted (bg-slate-500/20, bg-slate-400/300)
  — they are translucent/light badges that remain readable with dark text.
- Visual verification via the screenshot tool was not possible (it cannot
  authenticate into the demo tenant); correctness validated by CSS
  specificity/cascade reasoning, a clean /audit compile, and three rounds
  of architect review (final: pass).
- Unrelated backend ResponseValidationError (is_primary None in
  tenants_router) seen in logs is out of scope.
